dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2611  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Slitrks interact with PTPRS.\nKnock-down of PTPRS reduces excitatory synapse formation.\n\n19/2/2018 Pim\n- SLITRK1 is a known postsynaptic protein (see ticket #?????). It is shown to mediate cell-cell adhesion with PTPRS and PTPRD in a cell-adhesion assay (Fig.4A+B). SLITRK1 expressed in HEKcells is able to induce clustering of Glutamatergic and GABA ergic presynaptic (Synapsin1, VGLUT1, GAD67) but not postsynaptic (PSD-95) markers (Fig.4C+D).. Experimental description: Methods\nArtificial synapse-formation assays, cell-adhesion assays, and cell surface labeling assays were performed with HEK293T cells as previously described (22, 30). (ref.) Primary rat hippocampal neurons were cultured from E18 embryos.\n\nOverexpressed proteins:\n- \"pCDNA1-Slitrk3 encodes full-length mouse Slitrk3\"\n- \"pGW1-Slitrk3 encodes full-length human Slitrk3\"\n- \"pCMV5-Slitrk4 encodes full-length human Slitrk4\"\n- \"pCMV5-Slitrk5 encodes full-length Slitrk5\" (species not mentioned)\n- \"pCMV5-Slitrk1-monomeric Venus (mVenus) encodes full-length human Slitrk1\"\n- \"pCMV5-Slitrk2-mVenus encodes full-length human Slitrk2\"\n- human PTP-δ-Ecto (NM_002839, aa 21-1174) (traced back to PMID:20139422)\n- human PTP-σ-Ecto (NM_130854, aa 30-1167) (traced back to PMID:20139422)\n\n- Selected human species based on the overexpressed PTPRS in the cell-aggregation assay." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2611" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

